                <note rend="inline" type="source">622.116/119a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-08-12T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 12, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>110. The Department has been informed that the Ecuadoran Consul in New York has
                    been instructed to require exporters to present, beginning today, Ecuadoran
                    import licenses as a requisite for certification of documents.</p>
                <p>Please investigate and report by telegraph.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
